---

<section id="home" class="home">
	<div class="home-hero">
		<h1>Community-powered Bike Repair in New York City</h1>
		<p>
		The Time's Up Bike Co-Op exists to faciliate safe and sustainable transportation and life long appreciation of the simple beauty of the bicycle by 
		providing space, tools, and low-cost repair parts to empower cyclist of all backgrounds and experience levels as they learn all about their bikes.
		</p>
		<br>
		<p>
		The success of the this simple mission depends on volunteers who commit their time, talent and resources amid the other demands of modern life.
		Our comumunity is grateful for whatever you can contribute.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="info-grid">
		<section id="overview" class="info-card">
			<h2>Overview</h2>

			<p>
				We provide tools, parts, and peer-to-peer education so everyone can maintain their ride. Our
				shop operates on donations and mutual aid, which keeps the doors open and the wrenches turning
				for the entire community.
			</p>
			<img
				class="overview-hero"
				src="/repair-class.png"
				alt="Volunteers leading a bicycle repair class"
			/>

		</section>

		<section id="schedule" class="info-card">
			<h2>Schedule Overview</h2>
			<dl class="schedule-list">
				{schedule.map((item) => (
					<div class="schedule-item">
						<dt>{item.label}</dt>
						<dd>{item.detail}</dd>
					</div>
				))}
			</dl>
		</section>

		<section id="location" class="info-card">
			<h2>Location</h2>
			<img
				class="location-map"
				src="/timesup-location.png"
				alt="Map showing the Time's Up Bike Co-op location"
			/>
			<address>
				626 E 14th St<br />
				New York, NY 10009
			</address>
			<p>
				Find us in the East Village between Avenue B and C. Bike parking is available out front.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section id="join" class="info-card">
			<h2>How to Join</h2>
			<p>
			Time’s Up! is an all-volunteer environmental education and direct action non-profit group. Our Bike Co-op’s goal is to give everyone 
			enough knowledge to maintain their bikes, and hopefully, teach others to do the same.
			</p>
			<br>
			<p>
				There are many ways that you can volunteer and help Time’s Up!’s Bike Co-op. First and foremost, Time’s Up! 
				relies on a strong membership base, so if you have not joined already, please do so at our Membership Page. If you are 
				interested in becoming a mechanic, or in helping out with bicycle repair at the weekly workshops, e-mail <a href="mailto:contact@timesup.bike">contact@timesup.bike</a> 
				or drop by the Manhattan space (626 E 14th St.) on Wednesday or Sunday afternoons. We’ll pair you with a current mechanic 
				so you can learn the ropes of the space and gain hands-on maintenance skills. If you cannot schedule a specific time 
				for a committed volunteership, you can volunteer on an impromptu basis.
			</p>
			<br>
			<p>
				If you are interested in helping out at one of Time’s Up!’s group rides or other outdoor activities, e-mail 
				<a href="mailto:timesup.events@gmail.com">timesup.events@gmail.com</a>. Otherwise, the best thing you can do to help out 
				is show up to the workshops and events regularly. There’s always ample opportunity to contribute and make a difference!			
			</p>
		</section>

		<section id="contact" class="info-card contact-card">
			<h2>Email Us</h2>
			<p>
				Questions, collaboration ideas, or press inquiries? Drop us a line and we will get back to you
				within a couple of days.
			</p>
			<p class="contact-email">
				<a href="mailto:contact@timesup.bike">contact@timesup.bike</a>
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.home {
		padding: 96px 16px 120px;
		background: linear-gradient(140deg, #f8fafc 0%, #e0f2fe 50%, #fef3c7 100%);
